# ‚öôÔ∏è System Overview

The robotic vessel is a compact autonomous surface vehicle designed for [applications].

## 1. Features

- Dual-motor propulsion with differential steering
- GPS + IMU navigation
- WiFi/AP mode for manual control
- Autonomous waypoint tracking
- Powered by Raspberry Pi 4 + Python

---

## 2. Hardware Components

| Component        | Description              | Model / Spec          |
|------------------|--------------------------|------------------------|
| Hull             | Main body                | [Details]              |
| Microcontroller  | Central processor        | Raspberry Pi 4         |
| ESC              | Motor driver             | Dual 30A               |
| Motors           | DC propulsion            | 12V brushed            |
| Sensors          | GPS + IMU                | NEO-6M + MPU-9250      |
| Battery          | Power source             | 3S Li-ion, 5000mAh     |

---

## 3. Software Architecture

- Language: Python 3.10
- Modes:
  - Manual via onboard WiFi access point
  - Autonomous via waypoint file
- Key modules:
  - `navigation/` (GPS + heading)
  - `control/` (motor commands)
  - `web/` (manual interface)

---

## 4. Power & Wiring

**Power**:
- 3S Li-ion battery
- Custom distribution board
- Separate power rails for logic and motors

